4. An organization records three sets of IP addresses:
 L – logged in successfully
 F – failed login attempts
 B – blacklisted IP addresses

 Using set operations, identify:
 IPs that appear in both successful and failed logins but are not blacklisted.
 IPs that attempted access but never succeeded.
 IPs that are only blacklisted and never attempted login

L = {"172.16.16.200", "10.0.0.5"}
F = {"172.16.16.200", "172.16.0.2"}
B = {"172.16.0.2", "192.168.1.50"}
print("Logged in successfully",L)
print("Failed log in",F)
print("Blocked IP",B)
print("Both login types, not blocklisted:",(L&F)-B)
print("Attempted but never succeeded:",F-L)
print("Only blocklisted, never attempted:",B-(L|F))


