6.A university maintains collaboration records of students participating in multiple technical clubs. Each record is stored as a list of strings, where each string follows this format:
 StudentName:Club1,Club2,Club3
 records = ["Arun:AI,ML,Robotics",  "Bala:ML,IoT", "Chitra:AI,CyberSecurity", "Divya:Robotics,IoT,AI", "Ezhil:ML,CyberSecurity","Farah:AI,ML", "Ganesh:IoT,Robotics,AI",   "Hari:ML"]
 Write a Python program that performs the following operations strictly using combinations of lists, strings, and sets.
 Extract all unique student names into a set.
 Extract all unique clubs into a set.
 Convert each student’s club list into a set and store the mapping in a suitable data structure.
 Remove any duplicate club names if they appear due to formatting errors.
 Find students who are members of both AI and ML clubs.
 Find students who are members of AI but not Robotics.Identify clubs that no student belongs to alone (i.e., clubs that always appear with at least one other club).
 Determine the intersection of clubs for students whose names start with a vowel.
 Find the union of clubs for students whose names end with a consonant.
 Create a set of all characters used in all student names (ignore case).
 Find characters that appear in every student name.
 Identify students whose name character set is a subset of the character set of "Arun".
 Convert the list of club sets into a list and: Find duplicate club combinations (same set, different students). Count how many students share identical club memberships.
 Sort students based on: Number of clubs (descending), Then alphabetically (ascending)
 Create a final set of students who satisfy all of the following: Name length is a prime number, Member of at least one club starting with a vowel, Shares no common club with "Hari"


records = [
    "Abi:AI,ML,Robotics",
    "Nithya:ML,IoT",
    "Raji:AI,CyberSecurity",
    "Sridhar:Robotics,IoT,AI",
    "Mathi:ML,CyberSecurity",
    "Ramesh:AI,ML",
    "Ganesh:IoT,Robotics,AI",
    "Naren:ML"
]
student_names = set()
all_clubs = set()
student_clubs = {}
for record in records:
    name, clubs = record.split(":")
    club_set = set(clubs.split(","))
    student_names.add(name)
    student_clubs[name] = club_set
    for c in club_set:
        all_clubs.add(c)
print("\n1. Unique student names:")
print(student_names)
print()
print("\n2. Unique clubs:")
print(all_clubs)
print()
print("\n3. Student to club mapping:")
for name in student_clubs:
    print(name, ":", student_clubs[name])
print()
ai_ml = set()
for name in student_clubs:
    if "AI" in student_clubs[name] and "ML" in student_clubs[name]:
        ai_ml.add(name)
print("\n4. Students in both AI and ML:")
print(ai_ml)
print()
ai_not_robotics = set()
for name in student_clubs:
    if "AI" in student_clubs[name] and "Robotics" not in student_clubs[name]:
        ai_not_robotics.add(name)
print("\n5. Students in AI but not Robotics:")
